0. Files
	build            Folder for firmware building process
	CMakeLists.txt   The CMAKE config file to create the required Makefile
	main             Folder that contains the firmware source code
	sdkconfig        Project and device configuration


1. Description:
	This folder contains all needed files to build the project firmware

	Configuration
	=============
	This firmware is based on Espressif's MCU ESP32-S2 and in order to built it, you have to get and configure the esp-idf
	building environment. To complete the task, please, read the follow official documentation:
		https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/v5.3.1/esp32/get-started/index.html


	Firmware building:
	==================
	From the 5.3 release esp-idf uses CMAKE as software building infrastructure (project.mk is no more available).
	So, also for this project, all building rules are defined kin the CmakeLists,txt file.
	
	If you want to build a test, then you have to respect the following syntax,  when you create the Makefile. 
		FIRMWARETEST=<source file> cmake <CMakeLists.txt path>

